g.text: Smoothed line is from a generalized additive model with a Poisson family response, and is used to adjust
incidence numbers before analysis to estimate effective reproduction number. The lowest rate is 0.02%, and a
positivity rate of 1.5% would result in adjusted case numbers being 1.53 times their raw value.
Covid-19 test positivity in New South Wales, Australia, 2020
Data from NSW Health and The Guardian; analysis by http://freerangestats.info. Latest data is 2020-07-29.
